  <body>
    <p>In order to learn <a href="http://www.w3.org/XML/">XML</a> and
    <a href="http://www.w3.org/Style/XSL/">XSLT</a> I made a <a
    href="bbs.dtd">sgml dtd</a> to represent a bulletin board system.
    The I put into that markup a dialogue that took place on a bbs my
    freshman year at <a href="http://www.tntech.edu">Tennessee
    Tech</a>. Once I had a <a href="godbbs.xml">xml version</a> I
    wrote a <a href="bbs-html.xsl">stylesheet</a> to convert the bbs
    markup into html. Then I used the <a
    href="http://xml.apache.org">apache group</a>'s xslt processor
    called <a href="http://xml.apache.org/xalan">xalan</a> to generate
    a <a href="godbbs.html">html version</a>. This looks similar to
    the original <a href="godbbs.hand-coded.html">hand coded</a>
    version I did a couple years ago except all the numbering is done
    automatically as is the username aliasing.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="bbs.dtd">bbs.dtd</a></li>
